  "texts": [
    "Clearly some of the earlier implementations of baryon junctions [48,49], which attempted to match the earlier experimental data with certain parameter tunes, do not reproduce the experimental results presented in Fig. 9.",
    "Strangeness productionStrange hadrons serve as excellent probes for the physics of QCD phase boundary and search for the onset of deconfinement.",
    "Strangeness enhancement in heavy ion hadron collisions has long been suggested as a signature of the quark-gluon plasma [50][51][52], motivating its measurement in many experiments at different accelerator facilities.",
    "In general, the yields of strange hadrons in nuclear collisions are close to those expected from statistical models [53][54][55].",
    "The precise measurement of these yields in phase-I of RHIC BES experiments has led to a better understanding of the strange quark production mechanisms in nuclear collisions and a more reliable extraction of the chemical freeze-out parameters [32], as shown in Fig. 8."
